<frame cBy="296" cDate="01/20/2003 12:56:33 PST Mon" name="Permitting" ID="515" xsi:schemaLocation="../schema/frame.xsd" xmlns="http://framenet.icsi.berkeley.edu" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
    <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;In this frame a &lt;fen&gt;State_of_affairs&lt;/fen&gt; is permitted by a &lt;fen&gt;Principle&lt;/fen&gt;. Raising constructions are common in this frame. In this frame the &lt;fen&gt;Principle&lt;/fen&gt; which sanctions the &lt;fen&gt;State_of_affairs&lt;/fen&gt; is not an agent who grants permission to a specific individual or group of individuals, and thus differs from the Grantor in the Grant_permission frame. 

&lt;ex&gt; &lt;fex name="State_of_affairs"&gt;Children&lt;/fex&gt; were not &lt;t&gt;permitted&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="State_of_affairs"&gt;in the office&lt;/fex&gt; .&lt;/ex&gt; 
&lt;ex&gt; &lt;fex name="Principle"&gt;Code 1425&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;allows&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="State_of_affairs"&gt;us&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;fex name="State_of_affairs"&gt;to deduct interest payments&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;

&lt;ex&gt;&lt;fex name="Principle"&gt;No religion&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;accepts&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="State_of_affairs"&gt;discrimination against women&lt;/fex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;.&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
